File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:1045-1049

  static void peer_eui64_to_iid(const uint8_t eui64[8], uint8_t iid[8])
  {
      memcpy(iid, eui64, 8U);
      iid[0] ^= 0x02U;
  }

This XOR with 0x02 on the first byte is the IEEE 802.15.4 / RFC 4291 conversion from EUI-64 to IPv6 Interface Identifier. The 'universal/local' bit is flipped.

However, this is not documented in the code. A maintainer might not recognize this as a standard transformation.

Add a comment: // RFC 4291 Section 2.5.1: flip the universal/local bit for IID derivation
